The paper deals with the study of multi-input, multi-output (MIMO) interference and cognitive radio channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (IT) and networking and internet architecture (NI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the characterization of degrees of freedom (DoF) regions, which is a common topic in the signal processing (SI) and multimedia (MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of outer bounds, which is a common topic in the computer engineering (CE) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.SI, cs.MM, and cs.CE.
